{
  "doc_id": "33321",
  "text": "Mishra et al. demonstrated that inhalation of Aspergillus causes eosinophilic esophagitis, and further described that mice showed eosinophils migration to esophagus after allergen was challenged [CITATION_1] . In addition to sensitivity of food and seasonal allergies, a large series of patients were reviewed. In this study, out of 103 patients more than 73% with diagnosis of EE had positive family history of allergic diseases [CITATION_2] . Previous pediatric as well as adult studies have revealed association of more than 70-80 percent patient population having concurrent diagnosis of different allergic disorder with EE [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Children with food allergy to milk protein and eczema can have EE which can be missed in their diagnosis [CITATION_5] .",
